stylometry: Demand is always changing, the degree to which demand for a good or service varies as its price. Normally sales increses when drop in prices and decrease with rise in prices. As a general rule, cars and other non-essentials shows elasticity beacuse they are not always needed and can vary on demand. the essentials such as food and clothing are inelastic they are needed and the demand stays constant because people need these products to survive, they will pay the money for it because they need it. Elastic demand products are not needed to survive and people usually wait for the demand and prices to drop before purchasing these items.
